Project Structure

The program uses two main classes:

1. Student Class

This class represents a single student.

 Features:
Automatically generates a unique student ID
Stores:
Name
Course
Attendance
 Important Code:
id_counter = 1
This is a class variable
It ensures every student gets a unique ID
self.student_id = Student.id_counter
Student.id_counter += 1
Assigns ID and increases counter
 Methods:
update_attendance() → updates attendance
update_course() → updates course
display() → returns student details
2. AttendanceSystem Class

This class manages all students.

 Features:
Stores student objects in a list
Adds new students
Updates existing student records
Displays all students
Calculates average attendance
 Important Code:
self.students = []
List to store all student records
 Methods:
add_student() → adds new student
update_student() → updates student by ID
display_all_students() → shows all records
calculate_average_attendance() → calculates average
How the Program Works
Step 1: Create system
system = AttendanceSystem()
Step 2: Add students
system.add_student("Alice", "Math", 85)
system.add_student("Bob", "Science", 90)
Step 3: Display students
system.display_all_students()
Step 4: Update student
system.update_student(1, attendance=95)
Step 5: Calculate average
avg = system.calculate_average_attendance()
print(f"Average Attendance: {avg:.2f}%")
